_source.title: ODM Query Examples
_source.visState:
{"type":"markdown","params":{"markdown":"Here are some useful queries that you can copy/paste into the search bar above:

- to filter in exceptions only: `loglevel: "ERROR" OR loglevel:"SystemErr"`

- to filter in exceptions and warnings only: `loglevel: "ERROR" OR loglevel:"SystemErr" OR loglevel:"WARNING"`

- to filter in logs from Decision Server modules (keep/remove the module which you want/need): `module: /.*(common|mbean|persistence|execution|console|htds|dvs|cdi|engine).*/`

- to filter in logs from Decision Server about ruleset lifecycle events: `message: RESMGMT AND NOT (ibm_odm_ruleset.raw: "" OR ibm_odm_resmgmt_message: notification* OR ibm_odm_resmgmt_message: property*)`

- to filter in logs from Decision Center modules (only for modules with the complete path in the logs): `module: /.*(teamserver|decisioncenter).*/
`

- to filter in logs for a particular ruleset path, eg */myruleapp/1.0/myruleset/1.0*: ` ibm_odm_ruleset: "/myruleapp/1.0/myruleset/1.0"`
 
- to filter in logs for a particular ruleapp name, eg *myruleapp*: `ibm_odm_ruleapp_name: "myruleapp"`
 - the fields `ibm_odm_ruleapp_version`, `ibm_odm_ruleset_name`, `ibm_odm_ruleset_version` are also available"},"aggs":[],"listeners":{}}

_source.title: ODM Logs Histogram & ODM Modules Table Overview
_source.visState: {"type":"markdown","params":{"markdown":"Monitor the log levels of your logs across time using the **ODM Logs Histogram**. Click on a bar to filter for a particular log level and go to the top of the dashboard to apply it (tip: you can negate a filter by hovering over it and clicking on the minus magnifying glass). Use the **ODM Modules** table to identify the modules of those logs, and click on one to filter it in."},"aggs":[],"listeners":{}}

_source.title: ODM Rulesets Bar Charts Overview
_source.visState: {"type":"markdown","params":{"markdown":"Monitor the logs of your rulesets by log level using the **ODM Rulesets Bar Chart** graphs. The **ODM User Rulesets Bar Chart** bar chart shows your rulesets and the **ODM Internal Rulesets Bar Chart** shows rulesets created automatically by the Decision Center testing and simulation features. Click on a bar to filter in a particular log level and/or ruleset, go to the top of the dashboard to review the added filters, and apply the wanted one(s) (tip: you can negate a filter by hovering over it and clicking on the minus magnifying glass)."},"aggs":[],"listeners":{}}

_source.title: ODM Rulesets Lifecycle Pie Charts & Histograms Overviews
_source.visState: {"type":"markdown","params":{"markdown":"Monitor the lifecycle of your rulesets in the graphs below. The **ODM User Rulesets Lifecycle** graphs show your rulesets. The **ODM Internal Rulesets Lifecycle** graphs show rulesets created automatically by the Decision Center testing and simulation features. The pie charts are split by ruleset in the inner level and by lifecyle event in the outer level. The histograms shows you lifecycle events across time. Click on a slice or a bar to filter in a particular ruleset and/or lifecycle, review the filters that are added at the top of the dashboard, and apply the wanted one(s) (tip: to only view ruleset lifecycle logs in the table below, use the query provided in the example queries at the top of the dashboard)."},"aggs":[],"listeners":{}}

_source.title: ODMoC Dashboard Overview
_source.visState:
{"type":"markdown","params":{"markdown":"Use this dashboard to monitor your ODMoC logs. 

The dashboard is divided in three sections:
1. Tables: understand where the logs you are seeing are coming from. Filter in a particular tag, host, environment, instance, or template by clicking on a line in a table.
 - DC = Decision Center, DSC = Decision Server Console, DSV = Decision Server Validation, DSE = Decision Server Execution
2. Graphs: monitor trends across your environments and identify unwanted behaviors.
3. Logs: view the actual log data.

Note: any queries in your search bar or any filters that you add by clicking on the tables/graphs will apply to the entire dashboard."},"aggs":[],"listeners":{}}
